    <string name="resolution_info_message">The resolution setting affects video quality and performance:\n\n• CPU: Higher resolution = more processing power needed for video encoding\n\n• Battery: Higher resolution = more power consumption during use\n\n• FPS (Smoothness): On less powerful phones, high resolutions may cause frame drops. Lower resolution maintains stable 60 FPS\n\n• Bandwidth: Higher resolution = more data transferred over the network. Lower resolution improves stability on congested networks\n\nTip: Start with 720p (default) and adjust based on your phone\'s performance and connection quality.</string>
